      "span_text": "As a sensible indicator directly reflecting the burden of health payments in influencing household economy and causing impoverishment, we analyzed the incidence and intensity of catastrophic health spending. Catastrophic spending occurs when the ratio between total health expenditure and the difference between income and necessary expenditures such as accommodation, food, school, health care, clothing, water, electricity and sanitation exceeds 40% [CITATION_1] ."
